| ''DJ Mag''|| Top 100 DJs poll|| 1991–present|| The British dance music magazine ''DJ Mag'' publishes a yearly listing of the top 100 DJs in the world; from 1991 to 1996 the Top 100 poll were ranked by the magazine's journalists; in 1997 the poll became a public vote. The current number-one as of the 2017 list is Martin Garrix.<ref>cite web|title=Poll 2017: Top 100 DJs|url=https://djmag.com/top-100-djs/poll-2017|website=DJ Mag|publisher=Thrust Publishing|accessdate=22 February 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180222020740/https://djmag.com/top-100-djs/poll-2017|archivedate=22 February 2018</ref>
|-
| DJ Awards || Best DJ Award|| 1998–present|| The only global DJ awards event that nominates and awards international DJ's in 11 categories held annually in Ibiza, Spain, winners selected by a public vote<ref>cite news |last1=Rodriguez|first1=Krystal|title=Here are the winners of this year's Ibiza DJ Awards | date=23 September 2014| work = In the Mix Webzine Australia </ref> and one of the most important.<ref>cite news|last1=Zalokar|first1=Gregor|title=DJ Awards 2014 Winners|url=http://www.emfmag.net/articles/ibiza-dj-awards-2014-winners|work=EMF Magazine|accessdate=25 March 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402100810/http://www.emfmag.net/articles/ibiza-dj-awards-2014-winners/|archivedate=2 April 2015|df=</ref>
|- 
| Winter Music Conference|Winter Music Conference (WMC) || IDMA: International Dance Music Awards || 1998–present||<ref name=DJMagceremony>cite web|url=http://www.wintermusicconference.com/events/idmas/index.php?wmcyear=1998|title=30th Annual International Dance Music Awards—Winter Music Conference 2015—WMC 2015|work=Winter Music Conference</ref>
|-
| ''Project X'' Magazine|| Electronic Dance Music Awards|| 1995 || Readers of ''Project X'' magazine voted for the winners of the first (and only) "Electronic Dance Music Awards".<ref name=Billboard95>cite journal | journal = Billboard|date=August 12, 1995| author =Larry Flick |title= Gonzales Prepares More Batches of Bucketheads |page=24|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xAsEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA24&pg=PA24#v=onepage&q&f=false</ref> In a ceremony organized by the magazine and Nervous Records, award statues were given to Josh Wink|Winx, The Future Sound of London, Moby, Junior Vasquez, Danny Tenaglia, DJ Keoki, I.R.S. Records#Tribal America Records|TRIBAL America Records and Moonshine Records.<ref name=Billboard95/>
|-
| American Music Awards || American Music Award for Favorite Electronic Dance Music Artist|Favorite Electronic Dance Music Artist|| 2012–present || Most recently won (2017) by the Chainsmokers.<ref>cite web|title=2017 Winners|url=https://www.theamas.com/winners/2017-winners/|website=American Music Award|The American Music Awards|publisher=Dick Clark Productions|accessdate=22 February 2018</ref>
